{"id":1241298312,"question_id":2856,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"1 month, 2 weeks","timestamp":1714014077,"status":11,"status_display":"Wrong Answer","runtime":"N/A","url":"/submissions/detail/1241298312/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Count Complete Subarrays in an Array","memory":"N/A","code":"class Solution {\n    public int countCompleteSubarrays(int[] nums) {\n        \n        int len = nums.length;\n        \n        \n        Set<Integer> set = new HashSet<>();\n        for(int n : nums){\n            set.add(n);\n        }\n        \n        Map<Integer, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();\n        \n        int res = 0;\n        \n        \n        \n        int lastValid = -1;\n        for(int st=0; st<len; st++){\n            \n            boolean found = false;\n            for(int ed=Math.max(lastValid, st); ed<len; ed++){\n                \n                int n = nums[ed];\n                map.put(n, map.getOrDefault(n,0)+1);    \n                if(map.size()<set.size()) continue;\n                if(found==false){\n                    lastValid = ed;\n                    found = true;\n                }\n                    \n                res++;\n            }\n            map.put(nums[st], map.get(nums[st])-1);\n            if(map.get(nums[st])==0) map.remove(nums[st]);\n        }\n        \n        return res;\n        \n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"count-complete-subarrays-in-an-array","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
